title: RED RIVER SHOOTOUT

address.street: LAKE MURRAY STATE PARK - 13528 SCENIC STATE HWY 77

description:
Race # 3 of the GEAX Tour de Dirt 
Oklahoma’s State Championship XC Series 
Sunday, April 15th, 2014 
Lake Murray State Park Ardmore, OK 
Held under USA Cycling permit #2014-1042 
All USAC rules apply
course:
8.5 mile lap featuring 90% fast rolling single track through wooded terrain and rock gardens with moderate climbing. 
 Pre-riding: 
Trails always open when dry.  Race course will be marked by ?

                  Course will be marked with red polka dot ribbon hung on your right.  Course starts at the NE corner of the ball field.
registration:
Online registration is highly encouraged and opens March 1st and closes April 12th @ 9:00 AM register @ www.tourdedirt.org or usacycling.org.   
Race day registration is available for $5 additional, opens @ 8:00 AM and closes 30 minutes prior to your race start. 
Kids Kup registration (free) sign up race day only 

PRO & CAT 1 racers must hold an annual USAC license to race.  Non USAC member CAT 2 & 3 racers may race on a one day license. 

                           To qualify for Tour de Dirt series awards, CAT 1 & 2 racers must hold an annual USAC license. 

         Series points begin to accumulate only after annual license purchase.  CAT 3 racers will qualify for series awards using one day licenses. 

             A Tour de Dirt number plate is required to race in any Tour de Dirt series event.  These number plates are sold at all our events. 

               This is your number for the entire season.  You must present your number plate when registering for any Tour de Dirt event.
notes:
Prizes and awards: 
PRO, CAT 1 - 100% cash payout to 40% depth of field 
CAT 2, SS, CLYDE, 60+ open - award & merchandise 3 deep 
CAT 3 - award 3 deep, merchandise raffle 
Al’s Bicycles Kids Kup - medals
directions:
Take I-35 exit #29.  Drive east on Hwy 70 ~ 3 miles.  Turn right (flashing light) onto Hwy 77S. 
Drive south for ~ 2 miles.  Turn left at Duke’s Forest and proceed east to the race venue.   

Where to stay: 
Numerous motels in Ardmore.  Cabins, RV sites & camping (first come first serve) in Lake Murray State Park. 
Go to www.oklahomaparks.com for more info on Lake Murray State Park. 


More information: 
For more on TdD series rules, info and race updates check our web site and Face Book Page @ www.tourdedirt.org

title: Tour de Trykes Twilght Criterium
course: Course is a figure 8 with 8 corners in Downtown Enid Oklahoma. There is one demanding hill on the course and the finish is fast and flat.
registration: Registration opens on Jan 1, 2014 and closes on 08/14/2014. Late fee will be 10.00 additional and day of is 10.00 additional. One day license for cat 5 men and cat 4 women 10.00. Registration will open @ 4:00pm and close 15 min prior to the star of each race. Multiple entry with 5.00 discount on the 2nd or 3rd race.
notes: Awards will be given following the finish of each race. Top three must present themselves for podium immediately following the finish of their race. Results to USAC for ranking purposes. License must be presented for prize pick up. (team-club also)
directions: From south on I-35 go north to Hwy 412 into Enid. From North go south I-35 to Hwy 412 west into Enid. Plenty of parking on the perimeter of course
